OL,3,CMuch of Thwaites Glacier could be lost
OL,4,Cby 23rd century, experts say
OL,6,FExperts say the glacier and the wider
OL,7,Fregion, called the Amundsen Sea
OL,8,FEmbayment, account for 8% of the
OL,9,Fcurrent rate of global sea level rise
OL,10,Fof 4.6mm a year.
OL,12,FThe glacier is one of the largest and
OL,13,Ffastest-changing in the world, and if
OL,14,Fit collapsed entirely, sea levels
OL,15,Fwould rise by 65cm.
OL,17,FLatest computer models predict that
OL,18,Fice loss will accelerate through the
OL,19,F22nd century and could lead to a
OL,20,Fwidespread collapse of the West
OL,21,FAntarctic Ice Sheet in the 23rd.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
